Command Yuan-Ti	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:VoiceOfMerrshaulkTemplateTrait.SpecialQuality.SpellLike	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A Voice of Merrshaulk can command other yuan-ti at will, as dominate monster cast as a divine spell by a cleric of the cultist's class level (including cleric levels). This is a spell-like, mind-affecting compulsion effect.	KEY:Voice of Merrshaulk ~ Command Yuan-Ti				DEFINE:DominateMonsterLVL|0					BONUS:VAR|DominateMonsterLVL|YuanTiCultistLVL+ClericLVL									SPELLS:Class|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DominateMonseterLVL|Dominate Monster									SOURCEPAGE:SS																																																																																																																				
Improved Grab	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:FeralTemplateTrait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:If a feral creature hits an opponent that is at least one size category smaller than itself with a claw attack, it deals normal damage and attempts to start a grapple as a free action without provoking an attack of opportunity. If it gets a hold, it can rake if it has that ability (see below). Alternatively, it has the option to conduct the grapple normally, or simply use its claw to hold the opponent (-20 penalty on grapple check, but the feral creature is not considered grappled). In either case, each successful grapple check it makes during successive rounds automatically deals claw damage. See the MM for additional rules.	KEY:Feral ~ Improved Grab																											SOURCEPAGE:SS																																																																																																																				
Pounce	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:FeralTemplateTrait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:If a feral creature leaps upon a foe during the first round of combat, it can make a full attack even though it has already moved.	KEY:Feral ~ Pounce																											SOURCEPAGE:SS																																																																																																																				
Rake	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:FeralTemplateTrait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A feral creature that gets a hold can make two rake attacks at its full melee attack bonus with its hind legs. Each successful attack does normal claw damage for that size of feral creature, plus 1/2 its Strength bonus (rounded down). If the feral creature pounces on an opponent, it can also rake.	KEY:Feral ~ Rake																											SOURCEPAGE:SS																																																																																																																				
Rend	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:FeralTemplateTrait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A feral creature that hits with both claw attacks latches onto the opponent's body and tears the flesh. This automatically deals double the appropriate claw damage for that size feral creature, plus double the Strength modifier.	KEY:Feral ~ Rend																											SOURCEPAGE:SS																																																																																																																				
Acid	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:GelatinousTemplateTrait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:[Not Implemented] If the gelatinous creature hits with any of its natural attacks, it deals an additional amount of acid damage as set out in the table below.&nl;Fine 0  Large 1d6&nl;Diminutive 1 Huge 1d8&nl;Tiny 1d2 Gargantuan 2d4&nl;Small 1d3 Colossal 2d6&nl;Medium-size 1d4	KEY:Gelatinous ~ Acid																											SOURCEPAGE:SS																																																																																																																				
Resilient	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:GelatinousTemplateTrait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Gelatinous creatures have less defined shapes than the normal creatures they resemble. As a result, it is more difficult to score crippling or killing blows against them. A gelatinous creature:&nl;- Cannot be flanked;&nl- Takes 1d6 less damage from a successful sneak attack;&nl;- Takes one-half the additional damage dealt by a critical Hit.	KEY:Gelatinous ~ Resilient																											SOURCEPAGE:SS																																																																																																																				
Skills	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:GelatinousTemplateTrait.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A gelatinous creature receives a +4 racial bonus on Hide checks due to its translucent form.	KEY:Gelatinous ~ Skills									BONUS:SKILL|Hide|4|TYPE=Racial																		SOURCEPAGE:SS																																																																																																																				
Bloodcurdling Howl	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:GhostBruteTemplateTrait.GhostBruteAttack.SpecialAttack.Supernatural	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The mournful howling of a ghost brute chills the living to the core. The creature can howl as a standard action. All living creatures within a 30- foot radius must succeed on a Will save (DC %1) or Become Frightened for 2d4 rounds; those more than 30 feet away but Within 300 feet must succeed on a Will save or become shaken for 2d4 rounds. This is a sonic, necromantic, mind-affecting fear effect. A creature that successfully saves against the bloodcurdling howl cannot be affected by the same ghost brute's howl for one day.|BloodcurdlingHowlDC	KEY:Ghost Brute ~ Bloodcurdling Howl				DEFINE:BloodcurdlingHowlDC|0					BONUS:VAR|BloodcurdlingHowlDC|GhostBruteAbilityDC	BONUS:VAR|BloodcurdlingHowlDC|2|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Ability Focus (Bloodcurdling Howl)								ABILITY:Ability Focus|AUTOMATIC|Bloodcurdling Howl									SOURCEPAGE:SS																																																																																																																				
